cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.SY

This paper deals with distributed optimization, which is a common topic in machine learning and optimization. The privacy aspect of the problem suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of privacy-preserving machine learning, which is covered by cs.CR. However, the optimization aspect suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of random noise to achieve differential privacy suggests that it may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the fact that the optimization is done in a distributed manner suggests that it may also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.CR, followed by cs.IT, cs.DS, and cs.SY.
